<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('../partials/head', { title: 'Workflows & Action Routing' }) %>

    <body>
        <%- include('../partials/sidebar', { activePage: 'workflows' }) %>

            <main class="main-content">
                <div class="content-container">

                    <!-- Hero -->
                    <section class="hero-banner">
                        <span class="badge">Module</span>
                        <h1>Workflows</h1>
                        <p>
                            Workflows are <strong>Templates</strong> that define repeatable processes by attaching one
                            or more
                            <strong>Forms</strong>. Launching a template creates a <strong>Run</strong>. A Run generates
                            assignable
                            <strong>Items</strong> (task units) that appear in <strong>My Tasks</strong> for assigned
                            users.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <ul class="breadcrumbs">
                        <li><a href="/docs">Docs</a></li>
                        <li class="current">Workflows</li>
                    </ul>

                    <!-- Overview -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="workflows-overview">
                        <h2>Overview</h2>

                        <div class="panel panel-info">
                            <div class="panel-title">What this module does</div>
                            <p>
                                The Workflows module provides controlled execution of multi-step operational processes
                                inside the Automation Portal.
                                Admins define <strong>Workflow Templates</strong>, attach <strong>Forms</strong>, and
                                create <strong>Runs</strong>.
                                Runs generate <strong>Items</strong> that are assigned to specific users and completed
                                through form submissions.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="panel panel-warning">
                            <div class="panel-title">Template changes do not affect existing runs</div>
                            <p>
                                When a run is created, it “locks in” the template’s structure at that moment.
                                Template updates apply only to <strong>new runs</strong>. Existing runs remain unchanged
                                for auditability and consistency.
                                Yes, that means your past decisions are preserved forever.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <h3>What it solves</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Standardization:</strong> run the same process the same way every time.</li>
                            <li><strong>Accountability:</strong> work is assigned, tracked, and completed explicitly.
                            </li>
                            <li><strong>Admin visibility:</strong> admins can see progress across users without needing
                                status pings.</li>
                            <li><strong>Scalability:</strong> repeatable items allow the same step to be performed
                                multiple times within a single run.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>



                    <!-- Key Concepts -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="workflows-key-concepts">
                        <h2>Key Concepts</h2>

                        <details class="accordion" open>
                            <summary>Core entities</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <table>
                                    <thead>
                                        <tr>
                                            <th>Entity</th>
                                            <th>What it is</th>
                                            <th>Who manages it</th>
                                        </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Workflow Template</strong></td>
                                            <td>Reusable definition of a process (metadata + attached forms)</td>
                                            <td>Admin</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Template Form Attachment</strong></td>
                                            <td>Configuration tying a form to a template (required, repeatable,
                                                ordering)</td>
                                            <td>Admin</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Run</strong></td>
                                            <td>One execution instance created from a template</td>
                                            <td>Admin</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Item</strong></td>
                                            <td>Assignable unit of work inside a run (what users complete)</td>
                                            <td>Admin assigns, user completes</td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Repeatable forms</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    A repeatable form is a template attachment with <strong>Allow Multiple</strong>
                                    enabled.
                                    This allows multiple items of the same form to exist in a single run.
                                </p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Each item can be assigned to a different user.</li>
                                    <li>Admins can add more items later using <strong>Add Another</strong>.</li>
                                    <li>If a run is <strong>locked</strong>, new repeat items cannot be created.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Completion rules</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    A run is considered complete when <strong>all required items</strong> are either:
                                </p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Submitted</strong> (form response completed), or</li>
                                    <li><strong>Skipped</strong> (explicitly skipped by admin controls)</li>
                                </ul>

                                <div class="panel panel-warning">
                                    <div class="panel-title">Important</div>
                                    <p>
                                        “Not assigned” and “not started” are not completion states.
                                        If a required item exists, it must be completed or skipped.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </section>

                    <!-- Architecture -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="workflows-architecture">
                        <h2>Architecture</h2>
                        <div class="panel panel-info">
                            <div class="panel-title">Mental model</div>
                            <p>
                                <strong>Template</strong> = blueprint • <strong>Run</strong> = execution instance •
                                <strong>Item</strong> = assigned task •
                                <strong>My Tasks</strong> = user inbox
                            </p>
                        </div>



                        <details class="accordion" open>
                            <summary>High-level flow</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <ol>
                                    <li><strong>Admin creates a template</strong> and attaches forms.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Admin creates a run</strong> from the template.</li>
                                    <li><strong>System generates initial items</strong> based on attached forms.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Admin assigns items</strong> to users.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Users complete items</strong> by submitting form responses.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Admin monitors progress</strong> and manages lifecycle actions.</li>
                                </ol>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Visibility model</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Users</strong> see only items assigned to them in <strong>My
                                            Tasks</strong>.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Admins</strong> see the full run: items, assignments, progress, status,
                                        and controls.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <div class="panel panel-warning">
                                    <div class="panel-title">Backend enforcement</div>
                                    <p>
                                        This must be enforced server-side. Hiding buttons is not security, it’s theater.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Status model (Run + Item)</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    Status values should be consistent across UI and API so reporting and lifecycle
                                    logic stay predictable.
                                </p>

                                <table>
                                    <thead>
                                        <tr>
                                            <th>Object</th>
                                            <th>Status</th>
                                            <th>Meaning</th>
                                        </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Run</strong></td>
                                            <td>Active</td>
                                            <td>Run is ongoing and items can be completed</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Run</strong></td>
                                            <td>Locked</td>
                                            <td>Run is active but cannot create new repeat items</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Run</strong></td>
                                            <td>Completed</td>
                                            <td>All required items are submitted or skipped</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Run</strong></td>
                                            <td>Cancelled</td>
                                            <td>Run terminated by admin</td>
                                        </tr>

                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Item</strong></td>
                                            <td>Pending</td>
                                            <td>Item exists but not started</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Item</strong></td>
                                            <td>In Progress</td>
                                            <td>Item started by admin/user action</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Item</strong></td>
                                            <td>Submitted</td>
                                            <td>Form response submitted successfully</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Item</strong></td>
                                            <td>Skipped</td>
                                            <td>Item skipped by admin action</td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </section>

                    <!-- Admin Guide -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="workflows-admin-guide">
                        <h2>Admin Guide</h2>

                        <details class="accordion" open>
                            <summary>Workflow Templates screen</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Workflows</strong> to view templates.</li>
                                    <li>Select <strong>Create Workflow</strong> to define a new template.</li>
                                    <li>Templates should be set to <strong>Inactive</strong> instead of deleted when
                                        history matters.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion" open>
                            <summary>Template detail layout</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Left panel:</strong> template form attachments (configuration).</li>
                                    <li><strong>Right panel:</strong> list of runs created from this template (execution
                                        history).</li>
                                </ul>

                                <div>
                                    <div class="panel-title">Form attachment settings</div>
                                    <table>
                                        <thead>
                                            <tr>
                                                <th>Setting</th>
                                                <th>What it controls</th>
                                                <th>Why it matters</th>
                                            </tr>
                                        </thead>
                                        <tbody>
                                            <tr>
                                                <td><strong>Select Form</strong></td>
                                                <td>The form being attached</td>
                                                <td>Defines what users will complete</td>
                                            </tr>
                                            <tr>
                                                <td><strong>Default item name</strong></td>
                                                <td>Label shown for items created from this attachment</td>
                                                <td>Improves clarity in My Tasks and run tracking</td>
                                            </tr>
                                            <tr>
                                                <td><strong>Required</strong></td>
                                                <td>Whether the item must be completed or skipped</td>
                                                <td>Drives run completion rules</td>
                                            </tr>
                                            <tr>
                                                <td><strong>Allow Multiple</strong></td>
                                                <td>Whether repeatable items can be created</td>
                                                <td>Enables “Add Another” for scalable steps</td>
                                            </tr>
                                            <tr>
                                                <td><strong>Sort Order</strong></td>
                                                <td>Display order in run view</td>
                                                <td>Makes run readable and consistent</td>
                                            </tr>
                                        </tbody>
                                    </table>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion" open>
                            <summary>Create and manage Runs</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Open a workflow template.</li>
                                    <li>Select <strong>Create Run</strong>.</li>
                                    <li>System generates initial items based on template attachments.</li>
                                    <li>Assign items to users to make them appear in <strong>My Tasks</strong>.</li>
                                </ol>

                                <div class="panel panel-success">
                                    <div class="panel-title">Run-level admin controls</div>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><strong>Email Submitter:</strong> send status updates to run initiator.</li>
                                        <li><strong>Lock Run:</strong> prevents creation of new repeat items.</li>
                                        <li><strong>Cancel Run:</strong> terminates the run (recommended to capture a
                                            reason).</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Item actions within a Run</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <table>
                                    <thead>
                                        <tr>
                                            <th>Action</th>
                                            <th>Effect</th>
                                            <th>Notes</th>
                                        </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Assign User</strong></td>
                                            <td>Sets assignee</td>
                                            <td>Assignment controls visibility in My Tasks</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Start</strong></td>
                                            <td>Marks in progress</td>
                                            <td>Optional but useful for tracking</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Skip</strong></td>
                                            <td>Marks skipped</td>
                                            <td>Counts toward completion for required items</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Add Another</strong></td>
                                            <td>Creates additional item instance</td>
                                            <td>Only allowed if repeatable and run not locked</td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </section>

                    <!-- User Guide -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="workflows-user-guide">
                        <h2>User Guide</h2>

                        <details class="accordion" open>
                            <summary>My Tasks: where users work</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <ol>
                                    <li>Go to <strong>My Tasks</strong>.</li>
                                    <li>Select an assigned item.</li>
                                    <li>Complete the associated form.</li>
                                    <li>Submit your response.</li>
                                </ol>

                                <div class="panel panel-info">
                                    <div class="panel-title">What users can and can’t do</div>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><strong>Users can:</strong> complete assigned items and submit forms.</li>
                                        <li><strong>Users cannot:</strong> change templates, create runs, reassign
                                            items, lock/cancel runs.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Repeatable items (from a user perspective)</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    Repeatable forms may produce multiple similar items within the same run. You’ll only
                                    see the items assigned to you.
                                    If another repeat item is created and assigned to you later, it will appear as a new
                                    task.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </section>

                    <!-- Developer Documentation -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="workflows-developer-docs">
                        <h2>Developer Documentation</h2>

                        <details class="accordion" open>
                            <summary>Responsibilities (what the system must enforce)</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Template CRUD:</strong> create/edit templates with Active/Inactive
                                        status</li>
                                    <li><strong>Template attachments:</strong> attach forms with
                                        required/repeatable/sort order/default name</li>
                                    <li><strong>Run creation:</strong> snapshot template attachments into run + initial
                                        items</li>
                                    <li><strong>Item assignment:</strong> assigned_user_id drives My Tasks visibility
                                    </li>
                                    <li><strong>Item actions:</strong> assign/start/skip/add-repeat with rules enforced
                                    </li>
                                    <li><strong>Completion computation:</strong> required items submitted or skipped
                                    </li>
                                    <li><strong>Admin-only controls:</strong> lock/cancel/email tracking enforced by
                                        RBAC</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Data mapping (DB tables)</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <table>
                                    <thead>
                                        <tr>
                                            <th>Table</th>
                                            <th>Role</th>
                                            <th>Key relationships</th>
                                        </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>workflows</strong></td>
                                            <td>Template metadata</td>
                                            <td>Referenced by workflow_forms and workflow_runs</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>workflow_forms</strong></td>
                                            <td>Template ↔ Form attachments</td>
                                            <td>Referenced by workflow_items</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>workflow_runs</strong></td>
                                            <td>Run instance</td>
                                            <td>Parent of workflow_items</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>workflow_items</strong></td>
                                            <td>Assignable work units</td>
                                            <td>Assigned to users, tied to a run and attachment</td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>

                                <div class="panel panel-warning">
                                    <div class="panel-title">Immutability rule</div>
                                    <p>
                                        Do not “rebuild” run items if a template changes. Runs are historical execution
                                        snapshots.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </section>

                    <!-- Security -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="workflows-security">
                        <h2>Security & Permissions</h2>

                        <div class="panel panel-warning">
                            <div class="panel-title">Admin-only vs User operations</div>
                            <p>
                                Users complete assigned items. Admins control templates, runs, assignments, and
                                lifecycle.
                                Enforce permissions at the API layer. UI hiding is not permission enforcement.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <details class="accordion" open>
                            <summary>Admin permissions</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Create/edit templates</li>
                                    <li>Attach/configure forms (required/repeatable/order/default naming)</li>
                                    <li>Create runs</li>
                                    <li>Assign items to users</li>
                                    <li>Lock/cancel runs</li>
                                    <li>Email submitter / initiator</li>
                                    <li>View run-wide progress and item history</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>User permissions</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>View assigned items in My Tasks</li>
                                    <li>Open item and submit response</li>
                                    <li>View their own submission history (if allowed)</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </section>

                    <!-- Troubleshooting -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="workflows-troubleshooting">
                        <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

                        <details class="accordion" open>
                            <summary>Common problems</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <table>
                                    <thead>
                                        <tr>
                                            <th>Problem</th>
                                            <th>Most likely cause</th>
                                            <th>Fix</th>
                                        </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Task missing in My Tasks</strong></td>
                                            <td>Item is unassigned or assigned to someone else</td>
                                            <td>Admin must assign the item to the correct user</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Add Another not available</strong></td>
                                            <td>Form not repeatable OR run locked</td>
                                            <td>Enable Allow Multiple, or unlock run if policy allows</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Run won’t complete</strong></td>
                                            <td>Required item not submitted or skipped</td>
                                            <td>Complete or skip the required item</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Template edit didn’t update current run</strong></td>
                                            <td>By design</td>
                                            <td>Create a new run to use the updated template</td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </section>

                    <!-- FAQ -->
                    <section class="doc-section" id="workflows-faq">
                        <h2>FAQ</h2>

                        <details class="accordion" open>
                            <summary>Why didn’t my template edits update an existing run?</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    By design. Runs are snapshots of a template at the moment they were created.
                                    If template changes retroactively altered active runs, you’d lose auditability and
                                    consistency.
                                </p>
                                <div class="panel panel-info">
                                    <div class="panel-title">What to do instead</div>
                                    <p>
                                        Create a <strong>new run</strong> after updating the template. Existing runs
                                        remain unchanged.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Why can’t a user see a task in My Tasks?</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    My Tasks only shows items that are explicitly <strong>assigned</strong> to the
                                    logged-in user.
                                    If it’s missing, it’s almost always an assignment issue.
                                </p>
                                <table>
                                    <thead>
                                        <tr>
                                            <th>Symptom</th>
                                            <th>Likely cause</th>
                                            <th>Fix</th>
                                        </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Item not visible</td>
                                            <td>Item not assigned</td>
                                            <td>Admin must assign a user to the item</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Wrong user sees it</td>
                                            <td>Assigned to someone else</td>
                                            <td>Admin reassigns the item</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>User sees nothing</td>
                                            <td>User has zero assigned items</td>
                                            <td>Admin assigns at least one item in the run</td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>What does “Allow Multiple” actually do?</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    <strong>Allow Multiple</strong> makes a form attachment repeatable within a run.
                                    That means the run can contain <strong>multiple items</strong> based on the same
                                    form.
                                </p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Admins can create extra instances using <strong>Add Another</strong>.</li>
                                    <li>Each item can be assigned to different users.</li>
                                    <li>If a run is locked, new repeat items cannot be created.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Why is “Add Another” disabled?</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    “Add Another” is only allowed when the form attachment is repeatable and the run is
                                    not locked.
                                </p>
                                <table>
                                    <thead>
                                        <tr>
                                            <th>Reason</th>
                                            <th>Meaning</th>
                                            <th>Resolution</th>
                                        </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Form not repeatable</td>
                                            <td>Allow Multiple is off</td>
                                            <td>Enable Allow Multiple on the template attachment</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td>Run is locked</td>
                                            <td>Repeat creation disabled intentionally</td>
                                            <td>Unlock run (if policy allows) or create a new run</td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>When is a run considered “completed”?</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    A run is complete when <strong>all required items</strong> are either:
                                </p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Submitted</strong> (form response completed), or</li>
                                    <li><strong>Skipped</strong> (explicitly skipped by admin)</li>
                                </ul>

                                <div class="panel panel-warning">
                                    <div class="panel-title">Common reason runs don’t complete</div>
                                    <p>
                                        A required item exists but is still pending. “Not started” does not count as
                                        completion.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Can users assign tasks to other users?</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    No. Assignment is an <strong>admin-controlled</strong> operation.
                                    Users only complete what is assigned to them.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>What happens if a run is cancelled?</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    Cancelling a run ends the workflow execution early. Items should be treated as
                                    non-actionable after
                                    cancellation.
                                </p>
                                <div class="panel panel-info">
                                    <div class="panel-title">Recommendation</div>
                                    <p>
                                        Capture a cancellation reason to preserve operational context and prevent “why
                                        did this stop?”
                                        archaeology later.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Can a run have items assigned to multiple people at once?</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    A single item is assigned to one user at a time, but a run can contain many items,
                                    and those items can be distributed across multiple users.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </details>

                        <details class="accordion">
                            <summary>Can a user see the full run?</summary>
                            <div class="accordion-content">
                                <p>
                                    No. Users only see the items assigned to them in <strong>My Tasks</strong>.
                                    Admins have full visibility into the run lifecycle and all items.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </section>

                </div>
            </main>
    </body>

</html>